  "description": "Over-officer and owner of Gulilimiarisbeirgs' estate in Skredsvik. Nils passed his exam from secondary school in 1916 and his officer exam in 1918. He served in the Skaraborg regiment as an ensign from 1918, as a lieutenant from 1920, and as a captain from 1933. He was a deputy general staff officer from 1936, served in the Gotland Infantry Regiment nr 38 and was promoted to major in the general staff in 1940. He was appointed as a lieutenant colonel in the same year, served in the Life Grenadier Regiment and was appointed as a colonel in the reserve in 1947. He was the first adjutant to the chief of defense staff from 1937-1938, staff officer at the military command of Vilhelm III from 1940-1943. Nils was awarded the Orders of Vasa, Sword, and the Seraphim.",
